  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific laws targeting money laundering. In the United States, key anti-money laundering (AML) laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Report suspicious transactions\n2. Conduct customer due diligence\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Implement compliance programs\n5. Screen against terrorist watch lists\n\nInternationally, the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) sets global standards for combating money laundering and terrorist financing. Most developed countries have similar legal frameworks designed to detect and prevent financial crimes.\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution.",
